Generate and Test Your Web-to-Case Form

Generate HTML code that can be inserted into your company's website to capture cases in a web form.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Web-to-Case:	Customize Application
To generate Web-to-Case HTML	Customize Application

From Setup, enter Web-to-Case HTML Generator in the Quick Find box, then select Web-to-Case HTML Generator.
Select the fields to include on your Web-to-Case form.
Specify the complete URL to which customers are directed after they submit their information.
Enter the key pair that you obtained from Google and registered on the Salesforce Platform.

Leave Include reCAPTCHA in HTML selected.
Enable Server Fallback selected to prevent the loss of case traffic.

Click Generate.
Copy the generated HTML code and embed it into any page on your website.
Click Finished.

To test the Web-to-Case form, add the line <input type="hidden" name="debug" value="1"> to the code. This line redirects you to a debugging page when you submit the form. Don’t forget to remove it before publishing the Web-to-Case page on your website.
title: Generating Web-to-Case Forms in Service Cloud
